observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE direct the BAC to:

Ensure that the APP is filled-out following the step-by-step guide found on the GPPB website under downloadable forms;

Schedule each procurement activity with specificity, indicating the month, day and year;

Adopt competitive bidding (public bidding) as the general mode of procurement and resort only to alternative modes of procurement if all the conditions are met; and

Capacitate and keep themselves abreast of updates on procurement law and apply the same in the discharge of their duties and functions.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

request the Sangguniang Bayan to pass a resolution authorizing the transfer of School Buildings, Health Centers and Other Infrastructure Assets to the various recipients;

after the grant of authority, initiate the transfer by executing Deeds of Donation for the actual transfer;

ensure that acceptance shall be made by the beneficiaries;

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant with the coordination/help of Municipal Treasurer to:

Exert effort to collect these long outstanding receivables particularly the accounts with available reference documents by sending demand letters. Exhaust all remedies to collect and properly document efforts made;

Exert more effort to locate all related documents pertaining to the long outstanding receivables in order to establish their existence and validity;

For the receivables that are proven to be uncollectible but duly supported with required documents, we recommended that the Management file the request for authority to write-off dormant receivable accounts as prescribed under COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We further recommended that Management direct the LFC to fast track the policies and guidelines for the provision of allowance for impairment in accordance with IPSAS and thereafter for the Municipal Accountant to recognize allowance for impairment to present fairly the financial statements.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Human Resource Management Officer (HRMO) to:
Regularly provide to the Municipal Accountant, the list of separated, newly hired, and promoted employees as well as employees with salary adjustments and accordingly, provide all the necessary information needed in the updating of employee records with GSIS, Pag-IBIG, and PhilHealth;
Designate a staff in the HR Department who will conduct mandatory month-end inter-agency reconciliation with the Municipal Accountant using the eBCS Billing Statement, Pag-IBIG payment file template, and Employer’s Remittance Report before finalization of payroll; and,
Remind all employees that loan-related matters must be communicated to the HRMO such as when loans are already fully settled or restructured/renewed.
We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Regularly update employee records with GSIS, Pag-IBIG, and PhilHealth using the list of separated, newly hired, and promoted employees as well as employees with salary adjustments from the HRMO;
Provide to the HRMO, copies of eBCS Billing Statement and Employer’s Remittance Report of GSIS and PhilHealth, respectively, as basis in the preparation of payroll;
Ensure that the amount to be remitted to Pag-IBIG reconciles with the amount withheld by HRMO in the payroll. In case of noted variances, communicate the same with the HRMO; and
Exert additional effort to reconcile beginning balances of the inter-agency payable accounts – Due to GSIS, Due to Pag-IBIG, and Due to PhilHealth related to prior years’ transactions and address identified discrepancies for the current year, implement the necessary adjustments and promptly remit any outstanding balances.

We reiterated the prior year recommendations that the Municipal Mayor direct the BAC to:
Ensure that the APP is prepared in accordance with the guidelines and downloadable forms available on the GPPB website, consistent with the pertinent provisions of RA No. 9184 and GPPB Circular No. 07-2015;
Schedule each procurement activity with specificity, indicating the specific month, day, and year;
Adopt competitive bidding (public bidding) as the general mode of procurement and only resort to alternative modes if all the conditions set forth under Annex H of the 2016 revised IRR of RA 9184 are met;
Include all PAPs regardless of funding source;
Ensure that all personnel involved in procurement are capacitated and continuously updated on the latest developments in procurement laws and the proper preparation of the APP, applying such knowledge effectively in the discharge of their duties; and
Submit the supplemental APPs to support the PAPs which were not included in the original APP.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a.	request the Sangguniang Bayan to pass a resolution authorizing the transfer of School Buildings, Health Centers and Other Infrastructure Assets to the various recipients;

b.	After the grant of authority, initiate the transfer by executing Deeds of Donation for the actual transfer;

c.	Ensure that acceptance shall be made by the beneficiaries

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant with the coordination/help of Municipal Treasurer to:

a.	Exert effort to collect these long outstanding receivables particularly the accounts with available reference documents by sending demand letters. Exhaust all remedies to collect and properly document efforts made;

b.	Exert more effort to locate all related documents pertaining to the long outstanding receivables in order to establish their existence and validity;



For the receivables that are proven to be uncollectible but duly supported with required documents, we recommended that the Management file the request for authority to write-off dormant receivable accounts as prescribed under COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We further recommended that Management direct the LFC to fast track the policies and guidelines for the provision of allowance for impairment in accordance with IPSAS and thereafter for the Municipal Accountant to recognize allowance for impairment to present fairly the financial statements.

