We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the GFPS TWG to:

Reinforce the preparation of the GAD Plan and Budget with a more prudent gender analysis through establishing the cause/s of identified gender issues and thereafter formulate the PPA/s that directly address the same;

Leverage the available tools to strengthen gender assessment and the identification of beneficiaries of GAD PPAs such as the LGU GAD Database, CBMS and other tools mentioned in PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC No. 2013-01;

For instances when only a portion of a PPA is aligned with GAD, consider attributing the eligible portion to GAD through administering the Harmonized Gender and Development Guidelines (HGDG) while the non-eligible portion should be charged under a more appropriate fund.

We have recommended that the LCE being the Chairman of the Local School Board to:

convene earlier with the LSB for the timely review and approval of the SEF Budget to avoid delays in the implementation of the PPAs under the said fund;


direct the Municipal Budget Officer to assist the LSB in reviewing SEF budget particularly in the coming up with a more specific and detailed PPAs for appropriation;

instruct the Bids and Awards Committee to properly plan and schedule all procurement activities pertaining to educational projects for their timely implementation; and

direct the Municipal Accountant to review claims and their supporting documents before effecting payment.

We recommended and Management agreed to comply the following:

the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal General Service Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;

the Municipal Accountant to:
keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network;
prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of each year;

the Inventory Committee to:
conduct an inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the Municipality;
render a Report on the Physical count of the Road Networks System;

the Municipal General Service Officer to:
render a Report on Local Road Network and Road Map; and
keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components

We have recommended that Management:

enforce strict compliance with the guidelines in the granting, utilization and accounting of funds released to NGOs/POs as provided in COA Circular 2007-001;

stop from solely basing from their professional judgment the selection of deserving NGOs/POs who will receive grants for there are established guidelines for such;

require the NGO recipients to submit immediately the lacking documentations as mentioned above; and

prepare an addendum to the memorandum of agreement to include the lacking terms of reference as required by the Circular.

We have recommended that the LCE enjoin the:

Acting Municipal Accountant to discontinue the practice of having a fluctuating computation in granting the claims for the honoraria of the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) and Technical Working Group (TWG);

Acting Municipal Accountant to revisit DBM Budget Circular No. 2004-5A dated October 7, 2005 and adhere with the guidelines in computing the honoraria specifically in basing their claims in the number of successfully awarded projects;

Municipal Treasurer to facilitate the collection of refund of the excessive honoraria granted to the members; and

Acting Municipal Accountant to ensure that withholding taxes are deducted from payments of honoraria and the same be remitted to the BIR within the prescribed period.

