The Municipal Government could have benefited from its additional share from collections for Real Property Taxes (RPT) of as much as P 33,895,232.88 had the remedies provided under Section 174 of RA 7160 to enforce collection of delinquent taxes been availed of. 

We have recommended that the Acting Municipal Treasurer:

Continue to demand settlement of tax liabilities from the identified taxpayers;

Document the main reasons why these remained uncollected for the past years;

Adopt corresponding strategies to address the specific concerns of the taxpayers; and

In coordination with the Provincial Treasury Office, avail of the administrative and legal remedies provided by law to enforce collection of the delinquent real property taxes.

We recommended that Management:

Furnish a copy of BAC Resolution on the mode of procurement used for the procurement of consulting services;
Provide written justification on the failure to implement public bidding for the procurement of said consulting services;
Provide Detailed Estimate prepared by LGU as basis for ABC, Terms of Reference and other Deliverables. 
The Management to adopt Public bidding in the procurement of goods and services of the Municipality.

Furnish a copy of BAC Resolution on the mode of procurement used for the procurement of consulting services;
Provide written justification on the failure to implement public bidding for the procurement of said consulting services;
Provide Detailed Estimate prepared by LGU as basis for ABC, Terms of Reference and other Deliverables.
The Management to adopt Public bidding in the procurement of goods and services of the Municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:
•	Formulate plans and strategies to enhance collection of its delinquent real taxes;
•	Send demand letters to delinquent taxpayers to remind them of their obligations and avail of the administrative and legal remedies provided by law to enforce collection of the delinquent real taxes.
